In the office today with a car from Utah, k20z3. Before hitting the dyno we did a pre check and found the thermostat was stuck. Cut out the center and we were good to go. Made some adjustment to the tps and we hit the dyno. Was going to set boost at 12-14psi but found out that the boost controller is missing. Owner didn’t know it had been taken off the car. So we had to leave it on the gate 5.7psi making 315whp/212wtq. Not bad for an all stock engine. #redzonetuned #redzone #redzonehawaii #RZxDK

As many of you know, my wife and best friend @msctrn1 is part of AMSeven. She is the first car to be accepted in to and representing AM7 in 16 years. Being a part of this team is not taken lightly. There is more to it then just having a clean looking car. For those of you who have not been in the game very long, AM7 was and still is a graffiti crew that later started a Honda car crew in Southern California by @tackz_am7_tsl and @themightyeyesore in the late 90’s/00’s! The cars that were in this Era of the crew set the trends you know and love today such as engine bay tucks, shaved bays, wild color combos, and were street driven to every show. With such iconic builds like @tackz_am7_tsl’s Burgundy Ek coupe, Mike G’s Tank Eg, Noah’s black RHD SiR, @am7jeremy’s clean black DC Type-R, and Danny’s RedZone built 4dr RHD k series Ek just to name a few. With that being said, @msctrn1 is the latest edition…… until now! I am the now the newest member of AM7! I want to thank the team for the warm welcome and I can’t wait to be out with my car with everyone! #WeFamily #AM7 #AMSeven #AM7_Crew #IYKYK #RZxDK #RedZoneHawaii #LasVegas #RedZoneFamily #RedZone #RedZoneRace #DKGarage #4alana

There is a strong misconception when it comes to @msctrn1’s EK9, here they are below: 

1: THIS IS HER CAR, NOT MINE! she has had her hand on this build the entire way from start to finish. She chose the colors, she chose the parts, SHE Built the engine and head, she works on the car. I am the project manager, the Tuner, and the Support Team Leader. We had a small build team behind the car who helped us achieve this, those people know who they are! I DON’T own the car, we DON’T own the car, SHE owns the car, period. So when she wins at a show, congratulate HER, not me. I get my flowers from her and know she appreciates everything I do for this car. I’m sure no one congratulates her when my car wins a show…. 🤔 

2: This is a real EK9 Civic Type-R N1spec Edition. What this means for those that don’t know, Honda produced a version of the EK9 in Japan for the N1 Spec racing series. This model was a stripped down version of the original EK9 and came with EK4 interior, stock steel wheels, no power windows, no power door locks, no AC, and was 100KG lighter than the original EK9 that sports the red interior and amenities. 

3: Why did she decide to build off this chassis? Why not, it’s her car to do as she wishes, the come back is always “but the b16b engine! Why would you take it out!” First off, the car came without an engine when she got it, secondly, WHO THE FUCK CARES! It’s not your car, move along. 

4: We hear all the comments when people look at the car. “This car isn’t driven” “this car doesn’t run” “this car probably has no mileage on it” we’ll hate to burst all the bubbles of the people who think otherwise but this car has 10k miles on it already since it’s completion and it gets driven to Los Angeles and back from Las Vegas as well as driven around town and to San Diego a couple times. 

I hope those 4 little bits of fun facts was entertaining and gave you some insight on the car and her Owner!

I want to Congratulate My Wife, My Queen, My Best Friend for achieving best of show at the @usdmsupermeet Los Angeles Closer yesterday with Her 1997 N1 Spec Honda Civic Type-R! Yesterday as we were getting gas for the trip from Las Vegas to LA, we noticed we forgot to put the hood on the car, you see, @msctrn1 typically drives the car around town with no hood. So she never second guesses the hood being off when she drives the car to local shows or meets, that’s the norm for her, and when driving a long distance we would put the hood on to protect from bugs and rocks getting in the engine bay. So when we got to the gas station to gas up she had noticed that we forgot to put the hood back on, I asked her if she would like to go back to the house and put it on and she said “no, not really” so we both agreed on just making the 500 mile round trip Hoodless. The car made it to and from without issue with no hood and ran about 10°-15° cooler on temps compared to the other trips to SoCal. All in all, it was a great trip, awesome event, and fun times! Please congratulate my wife on bringing home 3 best of show USDM Supermeet trophy’s for 2023!!!! #amseven #am7 #redzonehawaii #redzone #redzonetuned #redzonediva #RZxDK #HerCTR #usdmsupermeet #Honda #Civic #typer #ek9 #n1spec #mermaidedition #kseries #usdmsupermeetcloser #itshercarnotminesoquitcongratulatingmeyoufakas
